cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on unsupervised domain adaptation for computer vision tasks, specifically on learning domain-invariant local feature patterns. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with multi-modal statistics, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which could suggest it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
